<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Colombian Armed Conflict Damages Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The four
decade-long civil war has caused huge personal and material
damages to Colombia.
</P>
<P>
The dynamiting of oil pipelines, the deforestation and
contamination with chemical herbicides applied to illicit
cultivations, and the presence of armed groups in protected
natural areas have turned nature into another victim of the
Colombian armed conflict.
</P>
<P>
A report of the Army News Agency published Saturday here says
that the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC) and the
National Liberation Army (ELN) guerrillas have dynamited more than
1,000 times the oil pipelines.
</P>
<P>
The Colombian Oil Company (ECOPETROL) has cleaned approximately
2,000 kilometers of rivers and 1,516 hectares of land affected by
oil spillages between 1986 and 1991.
</P>
<P>
But it has been almost impossible to recover the wildlife that
dies in oil pools, like fish and birds.
</P>
<P>
The document says that the attacks have caused several poor
zones of the country to miss receiving 900 million dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
