<HEADLINE> Zambian Minister Dies of illness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Zambian Local Government
Minister Bennie Mwiinga died of illness on Saturday at the age of
49.
</P>
<P>
Zambia National Broadcasting Corporation television quoted his
family as saying that Mwiinga died at a Johannesburg clinic in
South Africa.
</P>
<P>
Mwiinga started complaining of a cough and a flu two weeks ago
and was flown to South Africa for treatment last week.
</P>
<P>
Legal Affairs Minister Vincent Malambo flew to South Africa
this morning and he is expected to bring the body of Mwiinga to
Lusaka on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Mwiinga was a member of the former ruling United National
Independence Party led by former President Kenneth Kuanda before
he became one of the first members of the present ruling party,
the Movement for Multi-Party Democracy, which was set up in 1990
and won the multi-party elections one year later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
