<HEADLINE> Prize-winners' List of Venice Film Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The main prize-winners in the 56th
Venice film festival were as follows:
</P>
<P>
Golden Lion: "Not One Less" by Zhang Yimou
</P>
<P>
Special prize for directing: Zhang Yuan for "17 years"
</P>
<P>
Jury's Grand Prize: Abbas Kiarostami for "Le vent nous emportera
(The Wind Will Carry Us)
</P>
<P>
Volpi Cup for best actor: Jim Broadbent for "Topsy Turvy" by Mike
Leigh
</P>
<P>
Volpi Cup for best actress: Nathalie Baye for "Une liaison
pornographique" (A Pornographic Liaison) di Frederic Fonteyne
</P>
<P>
Marcello Mast:=xnirize for best emerging actor: Nina Proll for
"Nordrand" by Barbara Albert
</P>
<P>
Golden Medal from the Senate Presidency: "Rien a faire" (Nothing to
Do) by di Marion Vernoux
VenyNA'&AMP;ede for best first film: "Questo e' il giardino"
(This is the Garden) di Giovanni Davide Maderna
</P>
<P>
The jury awarded the Silver Lion for best short film to "Portrait
of young man drowning" by Teboho Mahlatsi and a special mention was
given to "Se-tong" by Heng Tang.
</P>
<P>
Other prizes awarded today included:
</P>
<P>
International Catholic Cinema Organisation prize: "Jesus's Son" by
Alison McClean; special ICCO prizes also to "A Week in the Life of a
Man by Jerzy Stuhr and "17 years" by Zhang Yuan.
</P>
<P>
National Union of Cinema Critics' prize: "Un uomo perbene" (An
Upright Man) by Maurizio Zaccaro; also best actor prize to Sergi Lopez
for A Pornographic Liaison and best actress to Valeri Brubni Tedeschi
for Nothing To Do.
</P>
<P>
Isvema prize, sponsored by National Union of Cinema Critics:
"Questo e' il Giardino" (This is the Garden). 
</P>
</TEXT>
