<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000GMT, Saturday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Arab League Secretary General
Esmat Abdel-Meguid urged Iraqi Foreign Minister Mohammed Saeed
al-Sahhaf on Saturday to make the upcoming Arab foreign ministers'
meeting a platform for reconciliation and objective resolutions.
</P>
<P>
Abdel-Meguid met with al-Sahhaf in the day to confer with him
on setting an agenda for the 112th session of the Arab League
Foreign Ministers Council, Egypt's Middle East News Agency (MENA)
reported. (BC-Arab League-Iraq)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY -- A senior Kuwaiti official said in the Saudi Red
Sea port city of Jeddah on Saturday that Kuwait supports Arab
unanimity and will attend the Arab League meeting due in Cairo on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"Kuwait cannot leg behind the Arab League or any other
important forums, as its issues will be defended at all forums,"
said Sulaiman Majid Al-Shaheen, Kuwaiti minister of state for
foreign affairs, on the sideline of the Gulf Cooperation Council
(GCC) foreign ministers' meeting in Jeddah.
</P>
<P>
He said the issue of Kuwaiti and third country nationals held
in captivity in Iraqi jails is on the agenda of the Arab League
meeting. (BC-Kuwait-Arab-Meeting)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- On the eve of the visit by Jordan's King Abdullah Bin
Hussein to the country, Lebanese Prime Minister Salim Hoss
Saturday highly praised his country's ties with the neighboring
Arab country.
</P>
<P>
"His (Jordanian King) coming visit indicates good and brotherly
 relationship which is linking Lebanon and Jordan," Hoss said in a
meeting with local guests.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the necessity to further strengthen the ties in
every field. (BC-Lebanon-Jordan)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY -- Foreign ministers of the Gulf Cooperation
Council (GCC) states welcomed on Saturday the new
Israeli-Palestinian peace agreement signed last week in the
Egyptian Red Sea resort of Sharm El-Sheikh.
</P>
<P>
In a final communique issued at the conclusion of their
two-day meeting in the Saudi Red Sea port city of Jeddah, the
ministers expressed hope that the Israeli government would fully
and precisely implement the agreement.
(BC-GCC-Peace-Reaction) 
</P>
