<HEADLINE> Cuba, Cambodia Plan to Resume Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Cuba and Cambodia plan to
resume bilateral cooperation in several fields with the signing
Friday of a memorandum of understanding for economic, scientific
and technological collaboration.
</P>
<P>
Cuban Foreign Minister Felipe Perez Roque and his Combodia's
counterpart Hor Namhong signed the document at a ceremony held
Friday in this capital during the visit of Cambodian Prime
Minister Hun Sen to the island.
</P>
