<HEADLINE> French Champagne Workers End Strike With Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The workers of champaigne wine
producing companies ended on Saturday their strike in the caves
and vineyards after their union reached an agreement with
employers on adopting the 35-hour work week, reported Agence
France-Presse (AFP).
</P>
<P>
The champagne wine workers started a strike on Thursday after
their employers refused to pay them full 40-hour salaries after
the adoption of the new work week system introduced by the
Socialist government.
</P>
<P>
The agreement will be formally signed by the union of
Confederation Generale du Travail and the employers of champagne
companies in Reims, north France, said AFP.  
</P>
</TEXT>
