<HEADLINE> SAARC Summit to Be Held in Late September: Nepali FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 11 (Xinhua) -- All member states of the
South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation (SAARC) have
agreed to hold the SAARC summit from September 26 to 28 in
Kathmandu, the Nepali foreign minister said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
When briefing journalists on the Indian foreign minister's
official visit to Nepal, Ram Mahat said he had consulted with all
member states except Bhutan and agreed on the date of the summit.
</P>
<P>
"All countries I visited expressed support for my proposal to
hold the summit on September 26-28," he said, adding that Bhutan
has agreed with this date too.
</P>
<P>
Mahat said that during his talks with the visiting Indian
Foreign Minister Jaswant Singh, they exchanged views on the
preparation for the forthcoming 11th SAARC summit. The Indian
foreign minister was here for an official visit from September 8
to 11.
</P>
<P>
The main topics of the summit will be the economic and social
agenda, such as trade, investment, economic cooperation and
poverty alleviation, said Mahat.
</P>
<P>
SAARC groups India, Pakistan, Bangladesh, Sri Lanka, Nepal, the
Maldives and Bhutan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
