<HEADLINE> Lebanese PM Praises Ties with Jordan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, September 11 (Xinhua) -- On the eve of the visit by
Jordan's King Abdullah Bin Hussein to the country, Lebanese Prime
Minister Salim Hoss Saturday highly praised his country's ties
with the neighboring Arab country.
</P>
<P>
"His (Jordanian King) coming visit indicates good and brotherly
relationship which is linking Lebanon and Jordan," Hoss said in a
meeting with local guests.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the necessity to further strengthen the ties in
every field.
</P>
<P>
At the invitation of Lebanese President Emile Lahoud,
Abudullah is expected to make an official visit to Lebanon on
Monday, the first by a Hashemite monarch in three decades.
</P>
<P>
Lahoud will also pay a visit to Jordan in May, the first by a
Lebanese head of state in 25 years.
</P>
<P>
During his two-day visit, the king will hold talks with
Lahoud, Hoss and House Speaker Nabih Berri on bilateral ties and
regional affairs.
</P>
<P>
Ties between Jordan and Lebanon have been improving, especially
after Syrian President Hafez al-Assad attended the late King
Hussein's funeral in February and the new king made a visit to
Damascus in April.
</P>
<P>
Lebanon has been following the foreign policy of Syria, a main
power broker which stations 35,000 troops in the country.
</P>
<P>
Ties between Jordan, Syria and Lebanon cooled after King
Hussein signed a peace treaty with Israel in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Lebanon and Syria are technically still at war with Israel
which is occupying South Lebanon and Syria's Golan Heights.
</P>
</TEXT>
