<HEADLINE> Most Trade Unionist in UK Oppose Euro: Poll </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Trade unionists in Britain are
not enthusiastic about early entry into the single currency,
according to a new opinion poll released Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The poll of 60 trade unionists conducted by the Transport and
General Workers showed 55 percent of trade union members were
opposed to the UK signing up to the euro.
</P>
<P>
Of those surveyed, 21 percent were strongly opposed and 34
percent were generally opposed although they said they could be
persuaded in favor if they thought it was good for the economy.
</P>
<P>
TGWU General Secretary Bill Morris said the survey lent support
to the government's current policy, saying "this poll clearly
shows there is no appetite for early entry."
</P>
<P>
"Any move to bounce the British public will be
counter-productive and could undermine the chances of a Yes vote
in a referendum," added Morris.
</P>
<P>
The issue of when Britain should join up to the single currency
is expected to be a key issue at next week's Trade Unions Congress
in Brighton. 
</P>
</TEXT>
