<HEADLINE> Paraguay Lowers Level of Relations With Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Paraguayan Foreign
Minister Jose Felix Ferenandez said Saturday that relations
between his country and Argentina are "virtually frozen."
</P>
<P>
Fernandez told the press that he ordered Paraguayan ambassador
in Buenos Aires Leila Rachid to reduce contacts with Argentine
diplomatic authorities to a third level, according to reports
received from Asuncion.
</P>
<P>
The relations between Argentina and Paraguay became tense after
the Argentine authorities refused their Paraguayan counterparts to
extradite former general Lino Oviedo.
</P>
<P>
Fernandez said that the Paraguayan government rejected the
apologies presented by Argentine President Carlos Menem after the
recent incidents between both countries.
</P>
<P>
Paraguay recalled its ambassador in Buenos Aires Leila Rachid
after Argentina refused to extradite Oviedo, the alleged
behind-the-scenes backer of the murder to Paruguy's former
president Luis Maria Argana, father of the current Paraguyan
Defense Minister Nelson Argana.
</P>
<P>
Menem cancelled a meeting with Paraguayan President Luis
Gonzalez Macchi foreseen for last Thursday in the Argentine city
of Posadas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
