<HEADLINE> Liberia Denies Attacking Guinea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Liberia denied Saturday an
accusation by neighboring Guinea that its troops in the border
area had attacked into the Guinean side and killed nearly 30
villagers.
</P>
<P>
Guinean state radio said Friday that the Liberian soldiers
attacked three villages in its Macenta region Friday, burning a
number of houses before they were driven back by Guinean troops.
</P>
<P>
The radio said one Liberian soldier was captured.
</P>
<P>
But, a Liberian senior military official, who didn't want to be
named, said in its capital Monrovia that Guinea's accusation was
aimed at spreading misleading information, according to reports
reaching here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
He said Liberia was not interested in war with its neighbors
but would defend its territory if attacked, adding that some
80,000 refugees were forced to flee fighting in the border region
last month, when armed insurgents believed to be Liberian
dissidents based in Guinea made assault in the Lofa county of
northern Liberia.
</P>
<P>
Liberia had accused Guinea of supporting the rebels, which was
rebuked by the Guinea's government. 
