<HEADLINE> Euador's President Announces Austerity Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Ecuadoran President Jamil
Mahuad said Saturday that his government will practice austerity
and budget discipline to reactivate the economy of the country in
the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
One of the government goals will be to reduce inflation from
55-60 percent this year to 25-30 percent in search of a three
percent economic growth in 2000, said Mahuad during a week-end
speech.
</P>
<P>
The president said that the 14-billion-dollar Ecuadoran foreign
debt is "a very heavy burden for the country, so the financial
authorities are seeking an agreement with the international
creditors.
</P>
<P>
He said that the country obtained new credits from the
international banking institutions for 1.25 billion dollars, but
it is necessary for the country to fulfill its part of the deal
and the restruction of its tax system.
</P>
<P>
The president said it is necessary that the Congress will
approve before November 30 the increase to the value added tax
(VAT) of 10 to 15 percent and the government budget for the year
2000 for the equivalent of 4.4 billion dollars. 
</P>
