<HEADLINE> Top Two Play to Goalless Draw in Chinese Soccer League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 12 (Xinhua) -- The much-touted top-of-the-
table Chinese first division soccer league clash between Liaoning
Fushun and Shandong Luneng turned out to be a goalless stalemate
on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Hosts Liaoning Fushun maintained their grip of the top spot on
44 points from 23 round of matches, with Shandong Luneng three
points adrift placing second.
</P>
<P>
Defending champions Dalian Wanda, who have had a nightmare
season so far with a abysmal 6-9-8 record, edged themselves out of
the relegation zone with a hard-fought 1-1 tie with third-placed
Sichuan Quanxing. Wanda was now lingering at five places from the
bottom in the 14-strong first division league, which wraps up
until after three more rounds of matches.
</P>
<P>
In today's other matches, Shenzhen Ping'an nipped Jilin Aodong
1-0; Qingdao Hainiu was held to a goalless draw by Guangzhou
Songri; Shanghai Shenhua scored a convincing 3-1 win over bottom
club Wuhan Heart K; Chongqing Longxing saw off Beijing Guo'an with
a 2-0 home victory; Tianjin Taida and Shenyang Haishi played to a
1-1 tie. 
</P>
</TEXT>
