<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Successes at Third China Investment And Trade Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Initial statistics showed a
total of 1,228 contracts were signed during the Third China
Investment and Trade Fair which ended here today.
</P>
<P>
These contracts are worth 5.183 billion U.S. dollars, 648 of
them in industrial projects, 178 in real estate and tourism, and
41 in infrastructure, according to spokesman Wen Zaixing for the
fair.
</P>
<P>
The fair has been held every year for the past 3 years in the
southeast China coastal city of Xiamen and is designed to attract
overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
New, high-tech projects have been the focus of overseas
investment and this year there were 112 high-tech project
agreements signed.
</P>
<P>
The number of visitors and delegations increased markedly, with
more than 6,400 visitors from over 80 countries and regions and
some 200 delegations attending this year's fair.
</P>
<P>
The city of Xiamen will hold the fourth such fair next year in
its new exhibition hall, the spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
