<HEADLINE> Escartin Crashes out of Tour of Spain Cycle Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Spanish climbing specialist
Fernando Escartin, third in this year's Tour de France, crashed
out of the Tour of Spain cycle race on Sunday after falling during
the eighth stage.
</P>
<P>
Escartin fell on the descent from La Cobertoria, the first of
three major climbs during Sunday's 175.6-km stage between Leon and
Col de L'Angliru.
</P>
<P>
Despite losing consciousness temporarily, the 31-year-old Kelme
rider attempted to continue the race, but had to pull out because
of pain in his wrist, shoulder and neck.
</P>
<P>
He was brought to hospital where he underwent examination.
</P>
<P>
The Spaniard finished 15th in the overall race standings, six
minutes 13 seconds behind the leader, his compatriot Abraham Olano.
