<HEADLINE> Importance of Legal System in Family Planning Emphasized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese family planning
workers today stressed it is very important to recognize the role
of a legal system in family planning and to act in accordance with
the law in supervising family planning.
</P>
<P>
This is closely connected with the country's population control
strategy for the 21 century, according to participants in a
meeting on strengthening the role of a legal system in family
planning held here today.
</P>
<P>
Since 1990, the State Family Planning Commission has had more
than 20 rules and regulations on family planning and all provinces,
municipalities, and autonomous regions, except for Xinjiang and
Tibet, have local laws.
</P>
<P>
More Chinese are willing to abide by the family planning laws
and regulations and have also learned how to resort to the law to
protect their rights and interests.
</P>
<P>
Yang Kuifu, Vice-Minister of the State Family Planning
Commission, said that the country's family planning laws are far
from perfect and that there are serious infringements of people's
rights.
</P>
<P>
Provinces, municipalities, and autonomous regions need more
concrete measures to get people to act in accordance with the laws
and to build a legal system for family planning.
</P>
<P>
According to him, the commission has proposed that the
framework of a national legal system on family planning be
initially built by the year 2005 and be basically perfected by
2015.  
</P>
</TEXT>
