<HEADLINE> Western China Appeals to Foreign Investors (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ma Xiuhong, assistant minister of the MOFTEC, announced a
series of new preferential policies to further encourage overseas
investment in the central and western parts including relaxation
of restrictions on overseas investors in joint ventures in the
region.
</P>
<P>
Taking advantage of this golden opportunity, provinces in
central and western parts of China have sent large delegations to
the current trade fair. Of the 18 press conferences given by the
organizing committee, 14 were hosted by provinces in the region.
</P>
<P>
Qinghai Province has provided overseas investors with 220
projects. Ningxia hui Autonomous Region invites overseas companies
to invest in agricultural, energy, communications and chemical
product development.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investors acknowledged their identical stance that
there is a great prospect in the development of central and
western parts of China. Capital cities, coastal cities, economic
development zones and state-listed high-tech development zones in
the region not only enjoy the same preferential treatments the
central government grants to coastal provinces, but also possess
many superiority in the development of agriculture, mineral
resources, tourism and raw materials compared with the former.
</P>
<P>
State Councilor Wu Yi promised big gains to overseas investors
so long as they invest in projects which can fully tap local
natural resources.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, the central and western parts
of China have been regions of the fastest development in recent
years. When national use of overseas investment in China dropped
in the first half of this year, investment in central part grew 7.
04 percent while that in the western part registered a 15.86
percent rise.
</P>
<P>
Chinese economists stated that many overseas companies would
move their funds and production bases to the central and western
parts in the near future as the labor force, raw materials and
production costs in coastal areas are spiraling.  
</P>
</TEXT>
