<HEADLINE> Track Coach Ma Misses Top Runners in City Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, China, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Famous track coach Ma
Junren arrived here this afternoon for the fourth Chinese City
Games without his top two women runners.
</P>
<P>
The absentees are Jiang Bo who missed the July trials and Dong
Yanmei who had a poor show in the trials in Shenyang, Liaoning
province.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Bo broke the 5,000-meter world junior record in the
previous City Games in 1995 while Dong Yanmei clocked a new world
record of 14:29.82 in the women's 5,000-meters in the 1997 Chinese
National Games.
</P>
<P>
With the absence of these two women runners, Lan Lixin, the 1,
500-meter world junior champion who clocked 4:10.05 in France in
July, 1998, becomes the gold medal favorite in the track
competitions to be started on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Besides, Ma's disciples will unveil a full-fledged battle in
the women's 800m, 1,500m, 5,000m and 10,000m track finals, as well
as in the field events of men's high jump and both men's and women
's hurdles.
</P>
<P>
Ma Junren stole the limelight in the world track arena in 1993
when his women disciples took titles in the 1993 world
championships in Stuttgart, Germany with two games records.
</P>
<P>
In September, 1993, three world records were created by his
women runners, including Wang Junxia and Qu Yunxia, in the 1,500m,
3,000m and 10,000m races at the seventh Chinese National Games in
Beijing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
