<HEADLINE> China Issues Forest Fire Alert </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 12 (Xinhua) -- The State Forestry
Administration (SFA) today asked for greater attention to
preventing forest fires in autumn.
</P>
<P>
According to analysis from meteorological departments, the
temperatures in north and northeast China this autumn are higher
than usual, and the heavy wind and dry weather will add to the
danger of forest fires.
</P>
<P>
During a recent meeting, SFA urged related departments of
forest areas in seven provinces, municipalities and autonomous
regions nationwide to intensify fire prevention efforts and
improve fire-fighting capabilities.
</P>
<P>
The administration stressed the need to control combustible
materials and prohibit field burning. Those violating the
regulations will face severe punishment.  
</P>
