<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Make All Chinese As Fit As Fiddle (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
They are all kinds of people from college students and
businessmen to soldiers and workers, as well as foreigners working
in Beijing, from billionaires to wage earners.
</P>
<P>
Getting to this place, however, was not so easy and Ma had
problems from the very beginning. Her lessons were borrowed from
western models, which were not particularly suited to easterners.
Many of her students, especially women who had never done any
exercise, found that their legs were getting stronger after taking
aerobics classes, and many complained that they didn't want to
look like athletes, Ma said, adding that the younger women wanted
slim, graceful bodies.
</P>
<P>
She had no choice but to find out what people wanted and how to
help them get it. So, she spent a few years doing research and
finally came up with a set of answers that would produce students
who were admired by both easterners and westerners.
</P>
<P>
But, she's still not content, and is planning a new program to
help all Chinese stay fit through a scientific way of life. This
goes far beyond body building and requires a healthy life and
scientific diet to make bodies more resistant to diseases.  (
more)
nnnn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
