<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mayweather Retains WBC Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 11 (Xinhua) -- American Floyd Mayweather
Jr. retained his World Boxing Council (WBC) super featherweight
title after beating Carlos Gerena of Puerto Rico in Las Vegas on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Mayweather is undefeated in 22 fights, winning 17 inside the
distance. He knocked Gerena down twice in the first round and
battered him in the seventh, after which referee Richard Steele
stopped the bout on the advice of ringside doctor Flip Homansky.
</P>
<P>
On the undercard, unbeaten World Boxing Association
featherweight champion Freddie Norwood survived a stiff test from
Mexico's Juan Manuel Marquez.
</P>
<P>
Norwood was given the nod on all three judges' scorecards, 114-
112, 117-112 and 115-111.
</P>
<P>
Norwood used a second-round knockdown to build an early lead
against Marquez. But the challenger rallied and floored the
champion in the ninth.
</P>
<P>
The fight could have gone either way as late as the 10th round
but all three judges gave Norwood the final two rounds, allowing
the champion to improve to 3-0 in title defences. 
</P>
</TEXT>
