<HEADLINE> Superbike World Champion Carl Fogarty Factfile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Following is a factfile on
superbike world champion Carl Fogarty:
</P>
<P>
Born: July 1, 1966. Blackburn, England.
</P>
<P>
1983 - Road race debut.
</P>
<P>
1988 - Winner of F1 title, Isle of Man TT races (Honda)
</P>
<P>
1989 - Winner of F1 title, Isle of Man TT (Honda)
</P>
<P>
1990 - Winner of F1 title, Isle of Man TT (Honda)
</P>
<P>
1991 - Enters world superbike championship on a Honda.Finishes
season in seventh place.
</P>
<P>
1992 - World endurance champion (Kawasaki). First superbike win
at Donington Park, England. Set new course record lap in Isle of
Man TT races.
</P>
<P>
1993 - 2nd in superbike championship (Ducati)
</P>
<P>
1994 - Superbike champion (Ducati)
</P>
<P>
1995 - Superbike champion (Ducati)
</P>
<P>
1996 - 4th in superbike championship (Honda)
</P>
<P>
1997 - 2nd in superbike championship
</P>
<P>
1998 - Superbike champion (Ducati)
</P>
<P>
1999 - Superbike champion (Ducati)
</P>
