<HEADLINE> Weapons Stolen From S. African Military Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 12 (Xinhua) -- High-caliber weapons,
including machine guns, grenades and rocket launchers, are being
stolen daily from the Tempe military base in Bloemfontein, Sunday
World newspaper reported.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that among the equipment stolen over the past
two months are 500 rifles, 200 boxes of ammunition and 150
pistols.
</P>
<P>
The weapons are being sold to criminal gangs, security
companies and farmers' commandos, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
It quoted soldiers as saying that vehicles, sophisticated
military equipment, combat uniforms, computers and even blankets
are finding their way out of the military base.
</P>
<P>
Intelligence agents and black soldiers believe that a clique of
right- wing soldiers with links to security and farmers'
organizations are at the heart of the theft ring, according to the
paper.
</P>
<P>
It quoted sources as saying that it often takes ages for
authorities at the base to discover that weapons are missing
because there is no computerized inventory system.  
</P>
</TEXT>
