<HEADLINE> Book Album on PRC Development Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 12 (Xinhua) -- A book album recording the
development course of the People's Republic of China (PRC) in the
past 50 years has come off the press in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin, general secretary of the Communist Party of China
(CPC) Central Committee, wrote in an inscription: "The founding of
the People's Republic of China has ushered in a new era in the
historical development of China. The Chinese people who have stood
up will contribute more still to the mankind."
</P>
<P>
The book was divided into five parts in the order of historical
development. They are the periods of the founding of the PRC,
arduous exploration, civil war years, reform and opening to the
outside world and forging ahead into the future. It has selected a
total of 2,124 photographs with 160,000-word captions.
</P>
<P>
The book depicts the hard yet heroic struggles of all ethnic
groups in China under the CPC's three generations' collective
leaderships toward the grand goal of turning China into a modern
socialist country.
</P>
<P>
The book album is compiled by the Museum of the Chinese
Revolution.  
</P>
</TEXT>
