<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Hongzhi's Fabrication of Life Story Exposed (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Li Hongzhi was born on July 7, 1952, in Gongzhuling City of
northeast China's Jilin Province. From 1960 to 1969, he studied
successively at local primary and secondary schools.
</P>
<P>
After 1970, he first worked at an army stud farm, and later
served as a trumpet player in a band of the Jilin Provincial
Forestry Armed Police Corps.
</P>
<P>
From 1978 to 1991, he worked as an attendant at a local
guesthouse run by the Jilin Provincial Forestry Armed Police Corps
and a member of the security section at the Changchun Municipal
Cereals and Oils Company.
</P>
<P>
Li Hongzhi began to propagate his ideas of "Falun Gong" cult
since the early 1990s. Initially, he fabricated the so-called "way
of practice" of "Falun Gong" by combining the movements of martial
arts he had learned from other people a few years before with
movements imitated from traditional Thai dancing.
</P>
<P>
Later, when he found that few people took interest in his "way
of practice," he changed the way of amassing money to treating
people with diseases by "exerting his energy potency".
</P>
<P>
But, cheating can never last long. After a period of scheming,
he concocted a set of lies and heretical theories of "Falun Gong"
and founded the "Falun Gong" organization with overtones of a cult.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990912.0118 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Hongzhi Uses Falun Gong to Amass Dirty Money (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Li Hongzhi has illegally
reaped a large amount of dirty money by using Falun Gong and
committed crimes of tax evasion, according to a newly-published
book here.
</P>
<P>
Initial investigations reveals that from May 1992 to the end of
1994, Li and his collaborators collected more than three million
yuan (360,000 U.S. dollars) through running Falun Gong training
classes.
</P>
<P>
"They paid no taxes on the overwhelming part of the money,"
says the book entitled "Li Hongzhi &AMP; His 'Falun Gong'-- Deceiving
the Public and Ruining Lives," which was published by the New Star
Publishers.
</P>
<P>
The major source of Li's illegal income was the production,
publication, distribution and sale of books, audio and video tapes
and VCDs on Falun Gong as well as clothing and other articles
needed for the practice of Falun Gong, the book reveals.
</P>
<P>
It listed several of Li's economic crimes. From June 1997 to
July 1998, the Wuhan Shenshen Group Co. in central Hubei Province
handed over to Li and his "Research Society of Falun Dafa" 1.2
million yuan and 10,000 U.S. dollars for publishing Falun Gong-
related materials, on which "no individual income tax was paid,"
according to the book.
</P>
<P>
In the five years following June 1994, the Shandong Scientific,
Technological and Cultural Service Center in east China's Shandong
Province realized a net profit of over 8.3 million yuan in
publishing audio-visual products on Falun Gong.
</P>
<P>
Now, it has been verified that the center had turned to the
society 700,000 yuan and to Li 90,000 yuan. In addition, it had
bought a "Santana" car for Li, who did not pay any income tax on
the amount he received.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990912.0119 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Hongzhi's Fabrication of Life Story Exposed (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"At the age of 12, the Taoist Master Baji Zhenren (Eight-Pole
Immortal) taught me Taoist practices. In 1972, I received Taoist
instructions from Master Zhendaozi (True Taoist), and in 1974, I
received further training in Buddhist cultivation and returned to
public life."
</P>
<P>
Books compiled by the "Falun Gong" organization stated, "At the
age of eight, Li Hongzhi attained the superb Great Law with great
supernatural powers, such as the ability to move objects (without
lifting a finger), fix articles (at whatever spot), control other
people's thinking and make himself invisible.
</P>
<P>
He understands the truth of the universe, has insights into
life and can see the past and future of mankind."
</P>
<P>
Li changed his date of birth from July 7, 1952 to May 13, 1951.
But the date of birth remained July 7, 1952 in the forms he
previously filled in for determining his grade on his unit's
payroll, applying to join the Communist Youth League and obtaining
his ID cards issued on December 31, 1986 and March 31, 1991
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The reason of Li's making this change was simply to deify
himself. In the Chinese lunar calendar, the eighth day of the
fourth lunar month is believed to be the birthday of Sakyamuni,
founder of Buddhism, and May 13, 1951 happened to be such a day.
</P>
<P>
Thus, by changing his date of birth, Li intended to indicate
that he is "a reincarnation of Skyamuni".
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he had a photograph taken of himself in a stage
costume he bought from a store to give himself the "image of
Buddha" sitting on a lotus flower.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990912.0120 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Hongzhi's Fabrication of Life Story Exposed (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In their reaction to his fabricated story of "spiritual
cultivation," their answers were either "nonsense," or "impossible
", or "I have never seen or heard of that."
</P>
<P>
His superiors and roommates at the stud farm and the forestry
police corps also said that he was just an ordinary serviceman in
an art troupe.
</P>
<P>
His colleagues at the local cereals and oils company also said
that Li Hongzhi knew nothing about the so-called "way of practice"
and "spiritual cultivation" at all before he joined a Qigong (a
system of movements and deep breathing exercises) training class
in 1988.
</P>
<P>
In general, no one who had been on familiar terms with him knew
anything about him acquiring the "miraculous abilities" he himself
boasted about.
</P>
<P>
When Li's acquaintances asked him why he made up his life story,
Li answered, "No one would believe me if I do not exaggerate a
little bit."
</P>
<P>
But these lies and completely-fallacious "miraculous abilities"
deceived many practitioners of "Falun Gong" who knew little about
him. 
</P>
</TEXT>
