<HEADLINE> Li Advocates Heretical Ideas to Control People's Minds: Book (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Li Hongzhi, founder of the
banned Falun Gong organization, advocated heretical ideas so as to
control the minds of Falun Gong practitioners, according to a new
book published here.
</P>
<P>
Li claimed that he was the sole savior of the present world and
that he and his "Falun Dafa" could ward off the "inevitable
disasters and sufferings of the doomsday world."
</P>
<P>
"He ordered the practitioners of Falun Gong to obey him
absolutely, and to think and act in strict accordance with his
teachings so that he could control their minds," says the book,
entitled "Li Hongzhi &AMP; His 'Falun Gong'-- Deceiving the Public and
Ruining Lives."
</P>
<P>
Li adopted all sorts of heretical means to control the
practitioners, resulting in the deaths of many practitioners and
serious damage to the health of many others.
</P>
<P>
Incomplete statistics show that 1,404 people have died as a
result of practicing Falun Gong, and still more have been found to
be suffering from mental disorders for the same reason, says the
book, which is published by the "New Star Publishers."
</P>
<P>
According to doctors at the Beijing University of Medical
Science, the number of patients with psychiatric disorders caused
by Falun Gong has increased markedly.
</P>
<P>
In 1992, Falun Gong patients accounted for 10.2 percent of all
patients suffering from mental disorders. In the first half of the
year, the number soared to 42.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
"Among those who died as a result of practicing Falun Gong,
some were deceived by Li Hongzhi's 'doctrine of karma', and
refused to either consult doctors or take medicine when they fell
ill," the book reveals.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
