<HEADLINE> Li Advocates Heretical Ideas to Control People's Minds: Book (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Others became mentally deranged in the course of practicing
Falun Gong. They either committed suicide or killed others, it
says.
</P>
<P>
What's more tragic is that some victims had put so much faith
in Li and his Falun Gong that they had let go untreated on his
orders and blamed themselves inwardly for not having enough faith
in "Master Li", the book says.
</P>
<P>
"Personal and family tragedies thus caused are too numerous to
mention one by one," the book adds.
</P>
<P>
"While Li Hongzhi told others not to consult doctors or take
medicine when they were sick, he did not himself practice what he
preached," it notes.
</P>
<P>
Many bills for reimbursement, turned in by Li and his family
members after consulting doctors and buying medicine, have been
found.
</P>
<P>
Now that his preposterous fallacies have been exposed, Li is
trying to deny that he advocated them. He himself had compiled,
printed and distributed books extolling such fallacies.
</P>
<P>
"How can he deny them when they are printed in black and white,
" the book asks.
</P>
<P>
"No responsible government in the world would tolerate a
heretical cult running rampant and depriving people of their lives
and health," the book notes, adding that Li can never escape
retribution for the crimes he has committed. 
