<DOCNO> XIE19990912.0146 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Tightens Control of Part-Time Insurance Agents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 12 (Xinhua) -- The China Insurance
Regulatory Commission (CIRC) today announced major measures to
further improve the management of part-time insurance agents.
</P>
<P>
The new measures came after a comprehensive review of all part-
time insurance agents' licenses, which began in March this year.
</P>
<P>
The new policy provides that each agent can only broker for
four insurers at the same time, among which, there can be only one
life insurer.
</P>
<P>
All the agents must strictly adhere to the contracts signed
with insurers and must not change any items on the policies,
neither can they lower or increase the premium, the commission
said.
</P>
<P>
Insurance firms must tighten control over their part-time
agents and must not employ any unauthorized part-time agents, it
added.
</P>
<P>
The CIRC warned that anyone caught violating any of these
regulations will be dealt with in an appropriate manner.
</P>
<P>
A telephone hot-line number has been made available to the
public for informing the commission of any violations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
