<HEADLINE> China Publishes New Book Exposing Falun Gong (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 12 (Xinhua) -- A new book aimed at helping
people know more about the banned Falun Gong organization and its
leader has come off press here recently.
</P>
<P>
The book, entitled "Li Hongzhi &AMP; His 'Falun Gong'-- Deceiving
the Public and Ruining Lives," provides basic information about
Falun Gong and its founder Li Hongzhi.
</P>
<P>
Published in both Chinese and English, the book also reveals
new facts of Li's law-breaking activities, such as tax evasion,
money laundering and visits to gambling clubs and brothels.
</P>
<P>
"Li Hongzhi has large amounts of savings deposits outside China,
and has committed crimes of tax evasion and money laundering," the
book says.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Government declared the Falun Gong organization
illegal on July 22, 1999. A week later, the Ministry of Public
Security issued a warrant for the arrest of Li Hongzhi.
</P>
<P>
Since mid-July, an overwhelming majority of former Falun Gong
practitioners have seen through the true faces of Falun Gong and
its founder Li Hongzhi, and broken away from the illegal
organization.
</P>
<P>
However, for those who have not followed media reports over the
past two months, this new book provides them with another chance
to know who Li Hongzhi is and what kind of organization Falun Gong
is.
</P>
<P>
"This book is a comprehensive examination of the facts about
this illegal organization, its sinister founder and its victims,"
according to the book's publisher "New Star Publishers."
</P>
<P>
The book, whose English version has 150 pages, consists of five
chapters, including Li Hongzhi and his fallacies, selected cases
of Falun Gong victims, and a list of deaths and dysphrenia
resulting from practicing Falun Gong.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
