<HEADLINE> Chile's Fishing Exports Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Chile's exports of fishing
products rose to 1.035 billion U.S. dollars during the first seven
months of this year, a 2.4 percent of increase over the same
period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Data from the Fishing Subsecretariat published Saturday say
that in terms of the export volume, the increase in the period is
10.7 percent over last year, corresponding to 679,008 tons.
</P>
<P>
Both figures show a continued trend in the recovery of the
fishing exporting sector, after falling demand especially of the
Asian region.
</P>
<P>
The data show the growing importance of the export of frozen
products, which increased by 16.4 percent to 506.8 million dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
