<HEADLINE> Inflation Up Slightly in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 12 (Xinhua) -- The inflation rate moved up
by 0.14 percentage points to 1.81 percent for the week that ended
on August 28 as edible oils and primary articles' prices continued
to rise.
</P>
<P>
According to the Reserve Bank of India, the annual inflation
rate, based on Wholesale Price Index, rose for the second
successive week to 1.81 percent from 1.67 percent the previous
week.
</P>
<P>
Inflation was at a higher level of 8.78 percent during the
corresponding period of last year, when prices of vegetables had
risen to unprecedented levels due to a shortfall in agricultural
production. 
</P>
</TEXT>
