<HEADLINE> India's Foreign Currency Assets Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 12 (Xinhua) -- India's foreign currency
assets (FCA) were marginally up by 10 million U.S. dollars to
30.379 billion U.S. dollars during the week that ended September
3, after a steep fall of 163 million U.S. dollars in the preceding
week.
</P>
<P>
According to Reserve Bank of India's weekly statistical
supplement, gold reserves were up by 5 million U.S. dollars to
2.659 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, total foreign exchange reserves rose by 15 million
U.S. dollars to 33.047 billion U.S. dollars. 
