<HEADLINE> Jiang, Putin Discuss Bilateral, International Issues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AUCKLAND, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang
Zemin and Russian Prime Minister Vladimir Putin discussed here on
Sunday Sino-Russian relations and regional and international
issues.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Jiang congratulated Putin on his
appointment as Russian Prime Minister and wished him success in
his work.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said friendly relations between the two countries are
developing continually and gratifying progress has been achieved
in bilateral cooperation in many fields.
</P>
<P>
Recalling his meeting with Russian President Boris Yeltsin in
Bishkek, Kyrgyz Republic, two weeks ago, Jiang said that the two
countries shared, on a broad basis, common interests and positions
on many major issues.
</P>
<P>
During the Bishkek meeting, the two presidents agreed to
further develop the Sino-Russian strategic partnership and
outlined priority fields for strategic coordination between the
two countries, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
The world should be multi-polar, Jiang said, both China and
Russia are supportive of multi-polarity and opposed to hegemony
and power politics in all forms and the two countries will make
further efforts to safeguard regional and world peace and
stability.
</P>
<P>
In autumn this year, Jiang and Russian President Boris Yeltsin
will hold another informal meeting in Beijing, the Chinese leader
revealed.
</P>
<P>
Both Jiang and Putin are here to attend the seventh informal
meeting of leaders of the 21-member Asia-Pacific Economic
Cooperation (APEC) forum scheduled for Sunday and Monday.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Putin told Jiang that the Russian
government highly appreciates its cooperation with China in all
fields, adding that the Russian government is of the view that
under the present international situation, Russia should establish
with China a strategic partnership in all respects and further
expand trade and economic cooperation with China.
</P>
<P>
Putin reiterated that Russia has always supported China's
position on the issue of Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
According to him, the Russian government has decided to
celebrate the 50th anniversary of the founding of the People's
Republic of China, which falls on October 1, and the 50th
anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic relations between
Russia and China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
