<HEADLINE> Five French Peacekeepers Killed in Kosovo Clashes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Five French peacekeepers
were killed during attacks Kosovo ethnic Albanians launched
against Serbs on Thursday, the Yugoslav official news agency
Tanjug reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The clashes in Mitrovica town, north of Kosovo, also left eight
ethnic Albanians dead and 30 Serbs injured, Tanjug said.
</P>
<P>
But at a press briefing on Saturday, a peacekeeping force
spokesman said 15 international peacekeepers were injured during
the clashes, without mentioning any deaths.
</P>
<P>
The international peace force released a statement on Saturday,
urging the two conflicting sides to calm down.
</P>
<P>
But tension in Mitrovica was not eased whatsoever on the day,
as hundreds of Serbs and ethnic Albanians kept throwing stones at
each other across the Ibar River, which divides Mitrovica town
into two parts, with Serbs living in the north and ethnic
Albanians in the south.
</P>
<P>
A group of ethnic Albanians stole into the north part on
Thursday night and launched mortar attacks on Serb residential
area, killing over 30 Serbs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
