<HEADLINE> More Efforts Needed to Fight Against Organized Crime </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Law experts attending the
16th International Conference for Law Enforcement agreed Saturday
that more efforts are needed to prevent and fight against rampant
organized crime.
</P>
<P>
Hungarian Chief Procurator Gyorgyi Kalman told a press
conference that during the six-day conference, 450 law experts
from 30 countries and regions did preparatory work for an accord
for coordinating international efforts against crime gangs.
</P>
<P>
Kalman said that organized crimes have become much more
diversified and dangerous taking advantage of the great
achievements in science and technology over the past 150 years,
such as crimes using Internet technology.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on money laundering for criminal rings by some
financial institutions, Kalman said international law enforcement
forces should have access to suspected secret bank accounts
whenever necessary. 
</P>
