<HEADLINE> Canadian Insurance Company to Form Venture Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 12 (Xinhua) -- The Sun Life Assurance
Company of Canada is expected to sell its first life insurance
policy in China during the second half of next year, according to
China Daily "Business Weekly" today.
</P>
<P>
The company gained approval from the China Insurance Regulatory
Commission in April to create a joint venture life insurance firm.
</P>
<P>
"We are actively seeking a joint venture partner," said Dkiran
Ohannessian, a company vice-president responsible for establishing
the venture.
</P>
<P>
He said some candidates, non-bank financial institutions, have
been identified and a final decision could be made in coming
months.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he said, the company is considering where it will
take its first step on entering the Chinese insurance market.
</P>
<P>
Sun Life has more choices than its predecessors in the business
because the country is opening another four cities including
Tianjin, Dalian, Chongqing and Shenzhen to join Shanghai and
Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
Sun Life's entry to the Chinese market is expected to result in
additional competition.
</P>
<P>
The entry of foreign insurance companies during the past few
years has provided an incentive for domestic insurance companies
to improve their services. This has created a larger market, the
Business Weekly says. 
</P>
