<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South China Region Leads Nation In Test Tube Cattle Breeding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, September 12 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region leads the nation in research on test tube cattle
breeding.
</P>
<P>
Three fourths of China's cattle produced in this way come from
the Institute for the Propagation of Animals, which is affiliated
with Guangxi University. Sources at the institute say that it has
produced 229 head of test tube cattle since September 1992, when
the country's first twin test tube calves were born.
</P>
<P>
Most of the cattle are produced for other provinces, autonomous
regions and municipalities. The survival rate is well over 80
percent. The institute has developed into China's biggest and most
advanced research center. The research is led by 36-year-old Shi
Deshun, the country's best-known animal breeder, who has a
doctorate from Dublin University in Ireland.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Shi says his institute can now mass producing cattle
embryos and has set up a high-tech business for this work.
Preparation is now underway for a center to produce cattle embryo
of fine breeds, which can provide cattle embryos and could produce
a big impact on the world's cattle-breeding business, he adds.
</P>
</TEXT>
