<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tianjin Strives to Be Industrial Base in Northeast Asia (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
And as one of the first 14 coastal cities open to foreign
countries in 1984, it now has 12,593 foreign-funded firms, with
contractual funding of 24.16 billion U.S.dollars, and 1.13 billion
in actual capital investment.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the industrial output value of such firms,
as a whole, accounts for more than 40 percent of the city's total,
and export volume over 70 percent.
</P>
<P>
Oceanic petro-chemistry, electronics, automobiles and machinery,
and metallurgy, are currently the four pillar industries for the
city. And some multinationals, such as the Motorola, the Samsung,
the Toyota, and the Otis, have entered these sectors.
</P>
<P>
"The eastward movement of industry, and the rationalization of
the industrial structure is underway now," said Li.
</P>
<P>
The Tianjin Coastal Development Zone, the Tianjin Economic
Development Area, and a group of large chemical enterprises have
all been set up in accordance with the city's strategy to move
the industry boom eastward.
</P>
<P>
The domestic output value of the Tianjin Coastal Development
Zone last year was above 30 percent of the total, industrial
output over 34 percent, exports volume more than 49 percent, with
electronics, modern metallurgy, petro-chemistry, and oceanic
chemistry as the main components.
</P>
<P>
"Tianjin is now striving to become a bridge between the
domestic and international markets, an exit for the Chinese
enterprises to the world, and a channel for overseas companies
into China," said Li.
</P>
<P>
He added that they will work hard to improve operations in
fields of retail business, real estate, finance, information
exchange, and agriculture, according to the international
standards.  
</P>
</TEXT>
