<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Investment in Tourism Soars in Costa Rica </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Investment in Costa Rica's
tourism industry grew 87.41 percent from January to June this year,
the Costa Rican Tourism Institute (ICT) said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
ICT Promotion Department data show that the biggest investment
increase in the sector occurred in lodging while growth was also
registered with new projects of accommodation and entertainment.
</P>
<P>
Investment for hotel-building went up from 247,000 U.S. dollars
in the first quarter of the year to more than 16 million dollars
in the second quarter.
</P>
<P>
Costa Rica received 500,000 tourists during the first half of
1999, said Eduardo Leon Paez, ICT executive chairman. He added
that he expects "Tourist One Million" in Costa Rica between
November and December.
</P>
<P>
Tourism is the main hard-currency earner for Costa Rica. Last
year, the income from tourism amounted to 812 million dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
