<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pearce Breaks Leg </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 11 (Xinhua) -- England defender Stuart Pearce
broke his leg in a match on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The injury, which he sustained during West Ham United's 1-0 win
over Watford, would threaten the veteran left-back's revived
premier league career.
</P>
<P>
West Ham United manager Harry Redknapp said Pearce had cracked
a bone in his leg after he was involved in a heavy tackle. "He's
broken his leg. He was running for a tackle and I heard a crack
at the time," said Redknapp. "He was right in front of the dugout.
"
</P>
<P>
Redknapp said Pearce, signed on a free transfer after former
Newcastle United manager Ruud Gullit made clear to the player that
he thought his career was over, would be out for "quite a while".
</P>
<P>
"He's been in such fantastic form for us and he's been such a
terrific lad to have around the place. The fans have taken to him
immediately...he'll be badly missed," added Redknapp.
</P>
<P>
Pearce, who won his England recall and 78th international cap
this month after a two-year absence, was turned down by a handful
of clubs before West Ham took him to help them through a defensive
injury crisis.
</P>
<P>
The injury left West Ham with a renewed crisis at the back,
with Ian Pearce out with knee ligament damage after being injured
on the opening day of the season.
</P>
<P>
Rio Ferdinand, Neil Ruddock and Scott Minto are also injured.
</P>
<P>
"We really are desperately short," said Redknapp. 
</P>
</TEXT>
