<HEADLINE> Manchester United Take Six-point Lead in Premier League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Defending champions Manchester
United jumped to a six-point lead after just seven matches in the
premier league season when they beat arch-rivals Liverpool 3-2 on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Newcastle United, with ex-England and Barcelona
coach Bobby Robson in charge for the first game, lost to Chelsea 1-
0 for a controversial penalty in the 37th minute, and they remain
second from bottom with just one point.
</P>
<P>
Croatian Davor Suker scored his first goal for Arsenal in the
final seconds of the first half before adding another in the
second half as Aston Villa, second at start of play, went down 3-1
at Highbury. Nwankwo Kanu scored Arsenal's third.
</P>
<P>
United have 19 points followed by Arsenal, Chelsea, Aston Villa,
West Ham United and Leeds United on 13. Chelsea and West Ham have
played only five games and, like United, are unbeaten.
</P>
<P>
Leeds beat Coventry City 4-3 in a thriller at Highfield Road
and West Ham downed Watford 1-0 thanks to a 47th minute goal from
Paolo di Canio.
</P>
<P>
Sheffield Wednesday remain at the bottom, with one point after
their sixth defeat, 2-0 at home to Everton. 
</P>
</TEXT>
